sec.p:
A non-perturbative string theory should have the ability to describe the dynamics of the background, and should be formulated in a background-independent way. String field theory (SFT) is a second-quantized string theory, where backgrounds are determined as classical solutions of the equation of motion (EOM). Since we can switch between backgrounds by shifting the string field, the background independence is also assured. Witten’s bosonic open string field theory (SFT) [
1
] is known for that its EOM being relatively easy to analyze classically.

app.title:
Appendix B. Proof of Eq. (
36
) ⇒ Eq. (
31
)

app.p:
In Sect.
3
, Eq. (
36
) was derived as a necessary condition for Eq. (
31
) by multiplying it by
B
from the left side. Here, we show that Eq. (
36
) is also sufficient for Eq. (
31
).

                    First, note that, using (Ξ
                    1,2
                    )
                    ‡
                    = Ξ
                    1,2
                    , the double conjugation of Eq. (
                    36
                    ) reads

                        (B1)

                            $$\begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{1}{\sqrt{Q_\mathrm{B}\xi ^1}}e^{-iQ_\mathrm{B}\xi ^2}c Be^{iK\Xi ^2}\sqrt{K\Xi ^1} =\frac{1}{\sqrt{K}}cB\sqrt{K} .
\end{eqnarray*}
$$


                    Plugging Eq. (
                    4
                    ) into the left-hand side of Eq. (
                    31
                    ) and using Eqs. (
                    36
                    ) and (
                    B1
                    ), we obtain

                        (B2)

                            $$\begin{eqnarray*}
&&\frac{1}{\sqrt{K(\xi )}}c(\xi )\frac{K(\xi )^2}{1 + K(\xi )}B(\xi )c(\xi )\frac{1}{\sqrt{K(\xi )}}\nonumber \\
&&\quad=\frac{1}{\sqrt{Q_\mathrm{B}\xi ^1}}e^{-iQ_\mathrm{B}\xi ^2}c e^{iK\Xi ^2}\sqrt{K\Xi ^1}\sqrt{K}\sigma \frac{1}{1+K}\bar{\sigma }\sqrt{K} \left(\sqrt{\Xi ^1K}e^{-i\Xi ^2K}Bc e^{iQ_\mathrm{B}\xi ^2}\frac{1}{\sqrt{Q_\mathrm{B}\xi ^1}} \right) \nonumber \\
&&\quad=\frac{1}{\sqrt{Q_\mathrm{B}\xi ^1}}e^{-iQ_\mathrm{B}\xi ^2}c e^{iK\Xi ^2}\sqrt{K\Xi ^1}\sqrt{K}\sigma \frac{1}{1+K}\bar{\sigma }KBc\frac{1}{\sqrt{K}} \nonumber \\
&&\quad= \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{Q_\mathrm{B}\xi ^1}}e^{-iQ_\mathrm{B}\xi ^2}cBe^{iK\Xi ^2}\sqrt{K\Xi ^1} \right) \sqrt{K}\sigma \frac{1}{1+K}\bar{\sigma }Kc\frac{1}{\sqrt{K}} \nonumber \\
&&\quad=\frac{1}{\sqrt{K}}cB\sqrt{K} \sqrt{K}\sigma \frac{1}{1+K}\bar{\sigma }Kc\frac{1}{\sqrt{K}} =\frac{1}{\sqrt{K}}cK\sigma \frac{B}{1+K}\bar{\sigma }Kc\frac{1}{\sqrt{K}} ,
\end{eqnarray*}
$$


                    which is nothing but the right-hand side of Eq. (
                    31
                    ). Note that we have used Eqs. (
                    36
                    ) and (
                    B1
                    ) at the second and the fifth equalities, respectively, for the quantities inside the parentheses.
